==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''re'' ('again'), and ''emergere'' derived from ''e''- (a variant of ''ex''-), meaning 'out, forth' and ''mergere'' meaning 'to dip'.

===Pronunciation===
* [[w:IPA_chart_for_English|IPA]]: /ɹi.i.'mɚdʒ/, [[w:SAMPA/English|SAMPA]]: /ri.i."m@`dZ/.

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|reemerg|ing}}

# to [[emerge]] again, to come into view after having hidden
# To come out of a situation, object or a liquid after having entered it.
#:''Example'': Soon after it submerged, the submarine reemerged from the ocean.

